## Source

This finding was identified through passive observation of publicly accessible internet scan datasets (Shodan, Censys, ZoomEye). I did not connect to the device or attempt to authenticate. I am not in possession of, and have not viewed or downloaded, any personal data from the exposed service.

## Concurrent notifications

I am sending the following concurrent notifications:

1. The apparent asset owner directly, by separate cover, with technical remediation guidance.
2. {{ ncert.authority_name }} at {{ ncert.email }} for coordinating technical remediation.

This notification to the National Privacy Commission is intended to support the Commission's mandate under Section 7 of RA 10173 to monitor and ensure compliance with the Act.

## Request

I respectfully request that the Commission:

1. Note this finding for monitoring purposes.
2. If the Commission deems it appropriate, exercise its Section 7(c) authority to compel the operator to investigate whether a personal data breach has occurred and notify affected data subjects in accordance with the Implementing Rules and Regulations.

I do not seek any further role in this matter beyond responsible notification. I am available to provide additional technical context to the Commission if it would assist.

